variables.value: Nobody shines brighter\nthan the baseball team!
Huh? Hey, it's your first day today?\nHeard of our school's track record and enrolled last minute, I bet.\nAn opportunist, aren't ya?
<MNT:NAGUMOHARA> Junior High is best known for its baseball team!\nLately, they've been flooded with registration forms\nfrom rookies chasing the big leagues.
It's a good school, but definitely not perfect.\nYou've heard about that <FLA:SAKURAZAKI>, right...?
You don't have to join\nif you don't want to.
Yeah, the football club's gone from <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>.\nIf you already know, then quit asking.
Football may be popular across the country,\nbut personally, I couldn't care less.
Football may be popular across the country,\nbut personally, I couldn't care less.
You heard of our school's track record and enrolled last minute, didn't you?\nAn opportunist, aren't ya?
<MNT:NAGUMOHARA> Junior High is best known for its baseball team!\nLately, they've been flooded with registration forms\nfrom rookies chasing the big leagues.
It's a good school, but definitely not perfect.\nYou've heard about that <FLA:SAKURAZAKI>, right...?
You wanna know more about that eyesore, <FLC:SAKURAZAKI>?\nCareful, you're biting off more than you can chew.
Word is, he even picks fights with street punks.\nGuy's a lost cause, no doubt about it.
<FLC:SAKURAZAKI>? Doesn't look it,\nbut he used to be real athletic.
What a mess.\nBet the student council's got their eye on you now.
Now that you know the secret...\nI can't just let you walk away.
Would you like to use the Match Simulation System?
Let me know whenever you're ready.
Shall we begin a Tryout Battle with Group A?
Let's start the Tryout Battle and see if anyone makes the team.
It's natural to hesitate.\nJust say the word when you're ready.
I know it's a tough call.\nAnyone stand out to you?
The incident from five years ago?\nStop poking around in the past.\nYou seem sharp, but you sure don't know when to drop it.
...The club back then was full of serious students like you.\nHard to believe they'd get involved in something like that...
Our school's one of Kyushu's top prep schools.\nPeople around here take a lot of pride in it.
But because of its fame, it's under constant scrutiny\nwhenever anything goes wrong...
The football club incident is a perfect example.
I'm not sure if it was the day of the incident,\nbut there was one occasion when everyone in the football club\nwent out to town together.
Then again, it was five years ago,\nso my memory might be playing tricks on me.
The football club's activity logs? The student council\nprobably keeps records of all the clubs somewhere...
I think they're stored in the Archive!
New spots to train, more ways to win.\nLet's get in top shape for that first match!
We've finally got a team of eleven.\nTime to play football for real.
Let's just start a Tryout Battle with group C!
Time to start the battle to see if anyone has it in them!
Not ready yet, huh? C'mon already!
Hard to pick, since they all stand out.
Now that the team's all here, things are heating up.\nLet's go win this!
The President never goes back on her word.
If we want the club officially approved,\nwe have to win that first match. Period.
Would you like to begin a Tryout Battle with Group B?
Let's start the Tryout Battle to decide who will join the club!
No need to rush.\nTell me when you're ready.
They're all unique in their own way,\nbut you need to judge them carefully.
Looks like turning the schoolyard into a football pitch\nwithout permission stirred up some trouble, but... oh well.
I can see it all—the matrix of the future.
I may be inexperienced, but I won't drag you all down...
No one can stop me once I start running.
It's just our first match. We'll push through, no problem.
Like the morning sun streaming through the window...\nThat's how I want the team to see me.
You've already stepped into my territory.\nYour fall is just seconds away.
I'm still figuring out what I can bring to the team...
It's a simple question for you.\nWho offers the greatest advantage? It's obvious, isn't it?
No need to worry about me.\nI'll carry out my role without fail.
Boo-yah! I'm <FLA:MAKUSHITA> from the sumo club!\nAiming to be champion in both sumo and football, yo!
You really look out for your teammates.\nColor me impressed.
I've always lived for the climb.\nLet's aim for the top together!
Thanks for your hard work! I'm giving it my all too—\ntotally fired up and training hard!
The way of the sword is the way of the heart.\nWanna test if I'm as sharp as my blade?
I'll work on building up my leg strength—gotta make myself useful.
This uncultured club needs someone as refined as me.
Oh, it's you.\nI've felt eyes on me... kinda gives me the creeps.
I enjoy helping those who give their all.\nBut this time, I want to be a player myself!
Nice work today!\nI'm touched you were worried about me!
I'm the calm before the storm right now.
Got this mysterious power, ya see.\nI see the ball you kick, clear as day.
Hey, <FST:UNMEI>, check this out—\nI'm in top form today!
If you want your metal to shine,\nface me head-on.
Metal shines brightest when it clashes.\nGoes without saying.
Yet even in lies, truth hides.\nTo test and be tested—that's mankind's nature.
Maybe I'm just pretending to practice...\nwhile plotting something else. Who knows?
You've got some nerve showing up near me again.
All set for the double showdowns?
Take all the time you need to get ready.
Search the school grounds for three spots\nwith unusual magnetic fields.
The app should alert you when you're near one.
Glossy, huh? You realize all our muscles are glossy, right? Yeah?
Wish I could get\nbetter at it.
It should be about\nthe keeper's handling...
I let you have it last time!
<FLC:UNMEI>, I need about three photos of <FLC:YAGYU> in mid-action,\nin a friendly against Twinford Junior High.
We've gotta stop their plan. I'm counting on you!
Let me know if you ever change your mind\nabout leading the <FLC:YAGYU> fanclub!
From now on, I'll fully support Sir <FLC:YAGYU> and the football he loves!
Eraser shavings... okay, maybe not those. But anything else works!
Why is he wandering around at night? I hope it's nothing bad...
<FLC:SHUNTA>'s out at night? No clue why.
But I did hear he's into something lately.\nCan't remember what it was, though...
Sigdor's Tale? Ohoho! Why, I'm reading it right now!
A book this good deserves to be shared!\nOf course I'll lend it to you.
Sigdor's Tale follows a fallen princess who forms a pact\nwith the Earth Goddess Siglia to reclaim her lost kingdom.
Make a pact with Siglia, and you become a Warrior of Sigdor—\nstrong as a thousand men. But it comes at a price...\nWhoops, spoiler alert!
I've been bulking up to attract new recruits!\nYou can see it, right?\nEven under the uniform—pure physique perfection!
Hey, you! Yeah, the throwable lightweight!\nWhy not join us? You'll be in good hands! Literally!
Focus on your center of mass... then drop!\nThe sumo stomp is deeper than it looks. Give it a shot!
Extraterrestrial communication—mysterious and fascinating!\nLooks like you've been drawn in, too.
Oh... it's you.\nI could really use your help.\nSwallowing my pride to ask, so please!
I'm busy watching my fave idol's concert.\nMaybe you're looking for someone to cheer on too?
Huh? You're offering a helping hand?\nTalk about perfect timing!
...I see. I understand your point.\nBefore we can join hands with aliens,\nwe must first join hands with one another.
Since you're the one proposing this idea,\nI'd like to have a deep discussion about space with you.
...Merging with the Space Laboratory?\nHow could we possibly relate to people\nwho treat sacred stars like research data?
Perfect timing... Let's hear your thoughts on\nwho gets to use the pool.
I can tell...\nYou're desperate for a cheer!
As a former Northbright fan,\n<MNT:NAGUMOHARA> has a long way to go.
Why can't you see the beauty?\nWhat's life without muscles?!
What?! You cheeky little—!\nYou won't get away next time!
You'll come to love it!\nFlesh against flesh—pure beauty.
Guess I'm on my own...\nStill, I have butterflies in my stomach.
Fine... I'll back off for now.\nBut you're joining... eventually!
That's too bad.\nHope you can join us next time!
I'll let you float... for now.
Ever in need of a boost?\nJust give us a shout!
What?! Ignoring my advice?!\nYou'll regret that!
Whoa! Those legs! That stance! Built like a tank!\nNow that's what I call bulk!
I always dream aliens will come crashing down\nto shatter this boring school life!
<FLC:MAKUSHITA>... that rookie's already picking fights with the upperclassmen?\nSomeone's gotta shut down that reckless mouth of his.
To us, space is Eden—\na place humanity must one day reach.\nBut you're saying just admiring it... is love too?
To truly love the stars, gazing isn't enough.\nYou have to see beyond... is that what you mean?
That CHAMP-ON top's blowing up online!\nFar as I'm concerned, CHAMP-ON's the top brand in Kyushu!
They just exude an air of confidence!
The baseball club's gear is insane.\nJust thinking about how future pros are training here fires me up!
I didn't think there was any bad blood between you and <FLC:YAGYU>.\nBut is there any tension now?
The baseball club's starters, playing football...?\nThink the teacher'll let it slide since they're the school's stars?
As a baseball fan, it's sad to lose <FLC:YAGYU>...\nBut I can't wait to see him crush it on the football team!
I heard the baseball guys helped with the school makeover!\nSo that's how they gave <FLC:YAGYU> a warm send-off...\nMan, that hits deep.
A lot of the baseball club's gear\nwas donated by <FLC:YAGYU>'s family!
That <FUL:UMIBOZU2>-style football machine is insane...\nWait—<FLC:MOMOCHI> set that up? No way!
Already a regular in seventh grade?
<FLC:MATSUDA> from the baseball club made regular in seventh grade—legend!\nBet he's grinding hard to catch the veterans.
The baseball club veterans are really hustling.\nI feel their energy... this year, they're trying to win it all!
I'm aiming to be\ntop of my grade!
Why not just go for it?
Someone like me\ncould never do it.
I'm just not good\nat this stuff...
I think I saw something\nabout them online.
I want to join the dance club and shine like <FST:RAIKA>...\nBut I'm sure they'd just turn down a loser like me anyway.
It's difficult to balance school and club activities...\nI'm just not sure I can pull it off...
I'm shocked at what you did at the schoolyard...\nYou don't look like it, but you're surprisingly feisty...
I always check the dance club's socials whenever they post.\nI'm too scared to join, but I still want to peek in on their sparkling world.
Yikes! W-Was that meant for me...?!
Your dance gave me courage.\nMaybe now I'll finally start chasing my dreams...
<FST:RAIKA> really stood out in that football match recently too.\nIt's amazing how she shines no matter what she does.
I went to cheer for <FST:RAIKA> at the West Manor match,\nbut I never thought I'd get to see <FUL:HARU> in person too...!
Club activities at <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> and Northbright are merging too...\nI bet a lot of them are gonna clash.
One of the teachers swears they saw <FUL:HARU> on campus.\nPretty sure it was just a mix-up, though...
Our next match is against Royal Academy, right?\nPeople on social media say their manager's a tactical genius.
Getting to the Football Frontier finals? That's huge...\nEspecially since the club's brand-new!
Hey, you—why don't you tell her to hang in there too?\nI think she just needs one last push.
Hey, who knows?\nMaybe it'll all work out. Isn't it worth the effort?
Looks like you can say goodbye to your nice student life.\nBut don't let that get you down!
She's been watching the dance club's videos\nevery day and she's already learned all the moves.\nAll that's left is for her to join. It'd be such a waste not to!
Hey! Don't scare my friend! And just so you know,\nI'm not about to back down from you, <LST:SAKURAZAKI>!
That football dance blew me away!\nI was Team <FST:RAIKA>, but I ended up voting for you!
I never thought you'd win that match in the schoolyard!\nCan't wait to see who you challenge next!
That <FUL:HARU> really is a football genius.\nEven I can tell—and I don't know the first thing about the game!
The Northbright football club really lucked out with the merger.\nGetting another shot at this year's Football Frontier? Unreal.
How's life over at Odaiba Football Garden?\nIf you ever feel like coming back, <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> is always waiting!
I couldn't take my eyes off that Keshin showdown with Stormridge.\nI think I see <FLC:KISOJI> in a whole new light now!
A diner near here said that if <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> wins,\nthey'll make everything on the menu free!
It's crucial <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> Junior High keeps its stellar rep.\nWe don't want troublemakers like <FLC:SAKURAZAKI> messing it up.
Even if the football club comes back,\nI'm not cheering for a team with a violence record.
This school's turning more football-centric by the day.\nFlexibility's a virtue, I guess.
Letting outsiders into our historic school? Hard to stomach, honestly.
What, got business at the Aquaculture Training Building?\nIf you're recruiting a marine bio club member, do it yourself.
Figures. Northbright's a top school\nlots of students know their youth football.
Hard to believe <FLA:SAKURAZAKI> is the school's poster boy now...\nPeople really do change, huh.
<FLC:SENNO>, the student council president, is our school's top beauty!\nOne look at her grace, and you're smitten for sure!
Executive Coordinator...\nA title worthy of <FLC:SENNO>! Sharp of mind, flawless in form!
Protecting these promising students is my duty,\nso I patrol the school grounds day and night,\nwatching for anything suspicious.
My work really starts after everyone else has left.\nYou'd better hurry home soon, too.
It doesn't matter how rowdy they are out of class.\nWhen that bell rings, the students settle right down and focus.\nThat's <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> for you.
I heard a gang caused trouble behind the noodle shop recently.\nBe careful not to get mixed up with any delinquents.
This time of day, every club is bursting with energy.\nJust watching them makes me feel younger.
The days are longer, but danger still lurks outside.\nDon't take any detours—head straight home.
I heard they finally cleaned up the old gym storage.\nI was sad to see it abandoned like that, so I'm glad.
The baseball team works hard,\nbut remodeling the yard in a day?\nThat's something else.
Changing schools in the middle of their studies\nmust be tough for those Northbright kids.
The Skycraft launch site caught me off guard.\nNever thought they'd put it there.
Oh, back from Football Gardens already?\nGot something you need here?
The whole school's all about football now.\nTimes sure are changing.
Finally joined the cheer squad!\nI've always dreamed of rocking that top.
<FLC:YAGYU>'s ears look amazing today, as always!\nOne day, I'll muster the courage to make eye contact...
I saw an article\nabout it online!
The baseball club gets all the hype!\nYou feel me?
I'd heard someone was joining Class A late, but I was hoping for a girl.\nDamn, Miss <LFC:KASUMISAKI> tricked me!
When I got hit in the face with a ball, I got laughed at—\n<FLC:YAGYU> gets the girls worried over a scratch!
Taking on <FLC:YAGYU>? That took guts...\nDo us uncool kids proud and knock him down a peg!
<FLC:SAKURAZAKI>! Uh, <LST:SAKURAZAKI>, sir!\nBig respect for landing a hit on that jerk <FLC:YAGYU>!
You, getting close with <FST:RAIKA>?\nI thought we were fellow uncool kids—you traitor!
<FLC:YAGYU> lost the match, so why is he still so popular?\nSeriously, I give up! There's just no understanding girls...!
<FUL:HARU> has probably been popular since birth...\nHe's on a whole different level. I'm not even jealous.
That Northbright senior, <FLC:TOMOBE>...\nBet the girls at our school are already buzzing about him!
Heard you're scouting for members...\nMake sure you aren't just chasing after cute girls, alright?
There's a girl who posted a selfie on the school app,\nbut I haven't seen anyone who looks like her around campus...
If I joined the football club,\nmaybe I'd get some cheers from the girls!\n...But honestly, the pressure'd probably kill me.
Can't help it, man. Guys like <FLC:YAGYU>?\nThey're on another level... far beyond us regular dudes.
You're the late transfer to Class A, right?\nCount yourself lucky getting <FUL:KASUMIN> as your homeroom teacher!
Yeah, the fans all think that <FLC:YAGYU> getting a scratch matters more\nthan our broken bones. All hail Lord <FLC:YAGYU> and whatnot...
Sounds like <FLC:YAGYU>'s fans are trash-talking you...\nBut I'm on your side.
You're always such a lone wolf, <FLC:SAKURAZAKI>.\nMakes a change to see you hang with others.
So <FST:RAIKA>'s in your crew now, huh?\nSurprise us in your next football match.
<FLC:SAKURAZAKI>, <FLC:YAGYU>, even the VP... all in the same club.\nManaging that crew's gotta be tough, but I'm rooting for you.
Talent doesn't always get passed down,\nbut at least <FUL:HARU> got the football skills.
Ninth grader <FLC:TOMOBE> was popular with the ladies at Northbright.\nWord is he was one of the most popular guys on the football team, too.
You're the hottest thing in school now.\nNo one's gonna complain if you go scouting for other clubs' members.
Since only <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> students can see the school app,\nI kinda let my guard down and overshared some stuff...
On game day, the whole class plans to watch the live stream together.\nBring your best, alright?
Comment allez-vous?\nYou're lookin' a little gloomy... Everything alright?
Bonjour, boy! Chasing <FUL:UMIBOZU> rumors too?\nHate to say it, but this pond's monster-free.
Hey, you! So you've gone and taken over the old gym storage?\nI gotta say, I admire that joie de vivre!
Mais pourquoi?! Mr. <LST:SEKOTA> got the boot outta nowhere...\nEven us teachers don't know what happened.
Ooh là là! Northbright's your next match?\nI'll be there with a banner, loud and proud!
Tres bien!\nThe gang's growing, and I'm all for it!
Félicitations! You've made it to the finals!\nThe whole staff's cheering you on!
No worries if you miss class during the tourney!\nWe already have some lovely summer catch-up sessions for you footballers!
Allez, allez! With this momentum, you're unstoppable!\nGo get 'em, <FLC:UNMEI>!
With his height, he stands out no matter where he goes.\nAnd with that fancy background? It's like the whole world's his playground.
Think he'll bust out 'Heavenly Thunder' again in the next match?\nThat move from the after-school show was amazing!
If <FLC:YAGYU>'s going all-in for the football team,\nthere's no way we're sitting this out!
So <FLC:YAGYU>'s played football before?\nWonder what kind of team he was on.
This new schoolyard... knowing the baseball guys helped out\nmakes me feel all warm and fuzzy inside.
Which angle should I film from on game day?\nGotta get a shot that makes the baseball boys shine!
The pitch looks fab, too!\nFootball practices are gonna look so good now!
Let's talk about the match instead!
No way a normal guy\ncould pull that off.
Can I get you anything?\nWater? A towel?
I poured my heart\ninto this letter!
The match is in Tokyo,\nisn't it?
We can take a night bus...
Can't believe we\nmade it this far...
One close to home\nwould be great.
I get winded just climbing the Hecaton Stairway...\nThink I could survive a sports club?
Hey, you're new here, aren't you?\nI hope you enjoy your new school life here at <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>!
That hair of yours... The school committee might come after you.\nUnless you're a stickler for style, I'd just get a short back and sides.
Gangs have been seen hanging around near school.\nStudents get targeted sometimes, so keep your guard up.
Friend, student and peer!\nLend me your opinion!
We're collecting responses for new features you'd like to see on <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>,\nour school's social media platform!\nIf you've got suggestions, we'd love to hear them!
Ah... I don't really check the app all that much.\nSorry I can't be of more help...
It looks like a really\ncool club!
Right? It's all tough\nfaces over there.
But that's the charm,\nyeah? Total appeal!
Seeing them tend flowers\njust feels so OOC.
What makes a gal...\na gal, anywho?
Omg I have to take\nsome pics!
One of the grads\nwent off the rails...
Hope they win the next match, too!
I can't wait for\nschool to finish!
What should we do\non game day?
We're waiting for the baseball team to show up...\nIt should be any second now!\nI'm so worked up, I think I'm gonna pass out!
Why you... How dare you speak to <FLC:YAGYU> in person!\nWe're still waiting for our turns!
Of all things, a football faceoff with the baseball club?!\nYou wanna take on <FLC:YAGYU>, do it in baseball!
Just don't speak to me right now, okay?!\nI'm busy burning my fave into my retinas!
<FLC:YAGYU>'s just... gone?! That was way too sudden!\nI wanna support everything he does, but it's complicated...
Thankfully, it's only <FLC:YAGYU> I'm into.\nIf I was crushing on the whole club, I'd be broke!
Picking a fight with the baseball club? You're nuts.
Still... why would <FLC:YAGYU> accept a football challenge, anyway?
Yeah, <FST:RAIKA>'s totally next-level gorgeous.\nBut the baseball team's got sparkle to spare too!
He looked amazing playing baseball...\nBut seeing <FLC:YAGYU> enjoy football\nwith that bright, beaming face? He really shone.
Feeling fancy.\nMight take the tram home.
Or maybe the bus\nso I can read...
I'm ready to run a lap.
No way the teachers\nstay quiet about it...
We gotta scout him\nfor the team!
But I'm not giving\nup my spot!
I admire those working\nfor big companies.
I don't know if I should\nsay...
Wow, things really turned\nout that way?
Really? I thought it was all right.
Heard they use some\npretty rare abilities, huh?
My father is a Tristar elite.\nWhat does your family do, eh? Heh...
I heard someone's picked a fight with the baseball club over football.\nDo you know anything about it?
I have an extra invite to the Tristar Heavy Industries event.\nI'm going with my father. Care to join?
My father tells me your dad's an outstanding businessman.\n<LST:SAKURAZAKI> Inc. is in good hands.
The old shipyard behind the station belongs to Tristar Heavy\nIndustries. It's a wreck now, but they plan to redevelop it soon.
Sounds like the baseball faction is in turmoil.\nEven the parents are shaken by what happened with <FLC:YAGYU>...
I heard there's been a major shake-up on the school board.\nI wonder what kind of chairperson would pull off such a bold move.
A friend from Tokyo's visiting soon.\nIt's their first time in Nagasaki,\nso I'm planning to show them the sights.
I hear Stormridge Junior High is from Kyoto.\nThey use something called a Keshin... can you use one too?
Royal Academy's that elite school with a forty-year\nundefeated streak in Football Frontier.
I never thought any school could beat Raimon...\nbut now, I'm hoping for an upset!
Hey there! If you have any interest in our matches, feel free\nto come watch! Tennis is, of course, the greatest sport ever!
The match is about to start, and everyone's all restless\nover gossip... Honestly, it's all your fault!
A football match? That's just barbaric!\nThis should be settled with tennis—the sport of the refined!
I started practicing tennis dance to learn new strategies!\nAnd I'll showcase elegant vocals, starring in my own musical!
The strategy you used last game was brilliant!\nI'd love your help crafting tennis strategies too!
I'd love to train with you all,\nbut we're busy gearing up for the tournament.\nJust hold tight a bit longer!
I joined the tennis club 'cause I heard it was full of rich kids...\nbut I just can't keep up with all that energy.
Even if we challenged the baseball team to tennis,\nwe'd still have a hard time. They're just built different...\nYou're kind of reckless, huh.
You've got some serious passion for sports.\nStarting a football team here, though? That's a terrible idea.
Is it true you're starting a football club?\nKinda jealous you've got something you care about that much.
All the buzz around the football club had me thinking about joining,\nbut you looked way too intense, so I backed off.
Think we're really up to being your practice partners?\nI dunno... but I've been kinda bored with tennis lately,\nso maybe this could be a nice change.
Man, the Northbright tennis club is seriously next level.\nAt this rate, I'm gonna lose my spot on the roster...
Out scouting for football players, huh?\nI bet there's some hidden talent in one of the culture clubs.
Didn't expect <FLC:KISOJI> to pull off a Keshin...\nGuess I should try a little harder in club, too.
If only I had something to throw myself into like you guys...\nthat's gotta be a fun way to spend your youth.
I'd crush you in\na battle of wits!
There was drama\nout on the field...
You're the one who\nmade a scene!
The 100-meter dash and marathons always get all the attention,\nbut we'll prove that hurdles are the best and secure club funding\nthat way!
Who cares about the baseball club?!\nWhat football competition?! Mind your own business!
If this keeps up, us hurdlers are gonna fade into the background.\nWe've got to make a statement in the next meet!
Other clubs are watching how we handle our gear.\nKeep it spotless—no excuses.
That seventh grader, <FLC:KAMEO>... his form caught my eye.\nNurture that kind of talent. Don't let it go to waste.
I heard <FLC:KAMEO> can glare like <FLC:SAKURAZAKI> and make people flinch...\nThat's just a rumor... right?
If there's one school I don't wanna face in a real match,\nit's Eastwind.\nThey crushed us in that joint practice... still stings.
No way he's cut\nout for that!
I hate that smug\nface of yours.
My phone...\ncould it be on the roof?
My train pass...\ndid I leave it in class?
Gotta book it to\nthe study room!
I'm gonna be late\nfor cram school...
I'll just ask a member\nof the cleanup crew...
I want to get\nclose to them...
But will I even \nget a chance to say hi?
How am I gonna\ncarry it all?
Did you hear\nabout the chairman of...
Oh my god, this is\nso wild!
And right at the start\nof the school year, too!
Even the teachers won't\nstop talking about it!
I can't wait to see\nwhat happens!
They say she's a\ntotal muscle freak!
Hey, did you hear the rumors\nabout the Idol-lovers club?
I hear their relationship charts are a complicated mess.\nIt's tough when your whole world's this small.
Whoa! The guy behind you—how'd you tame him?!\nMind control?
<FUL:MOMOCHI>'s the heiress to a protein company, right?\nNo wonder she knows all about body sculpting.
Wait, are you trying to crash our conversation?\nKinda caught me off guard.
Hey, did you hear why Vice-Principal <LST:SEKOTA> disappeared?\nSorry, I have no clue either.
Yeah, school love lives really should be cherished.
Come to think of it, you're also new. What do you think?\nAny chance you'll find the one for you?
Someone on the baseball team stole your crush, right?\nThat's why you took on that crazy challenge. I see right through you!
She's into muscles, so her boyfriend's gotta be jacked too.\nOr maybe she's already got a muscle-bound fiancé?!
Uh, we were just talking about love...\nYou wanna join?
I bet <LST:SEKOTA> got caught up in some forbidden affair.\nYeah, he ran off with his lover. I'm sure of it!
Hey, you! Don't just ignore me! We made eye contact!
I'm awful with this love stuff...\nPlease, you have to help me get through this.
